1.)  They choose to move out to space, because other people are moving out to space and finding lots of new opputunities, while the two teens' parents, want to keep them on Earth.  The parents are very strict, like, no dating, no being out past dark, and certainly no going out into space (why will be adressed later).  They pretty much feel stifled on Earth.  Plus they want to get away from their parents.<br>
<br>
2.)   Earth is pretty much the same, it's got futuristic crap and all though.  The only difference is that the population is rapidly decreasing, because people all want to move out to space.  Humanity has spread to the moon and Mars.  I noticed in Cowboy Bebop, people lived in places that would be imposible for people to live, like Venus, it's surrounded by sulfuric acid clouds, that's not good, or on Jupiter, the gravity is too strong.  All the major cities are on planets, but there are civilizations built floating in space.  Some are big, some are little.  The teens live in a little one.<br>
<br>
3.)   A male friend of one of the girls says he will take them out to find somewhere to live in his little space ship thingy (what are those called?!) if they pay him.  He has really deadbeat parents, so they don't care what he does.  The economy of the planets differs from planet to planet, Earth and the moon are wealthy, being close allies with one another.  But Mars is the one they don't like.  Mars's conditions are pretty crappy, and the people there are rougher than normal.  They travel with those little personal space ships, which can be used in space but also on planets.<br>
<br>
4.)  The space station was built by the Russians back on Earth about 5 years before they go looking.  When one of the Russian guys dies in an accident, the other guys on the space station think they see his ghost, and they freak out, and abandon the space station and head back to Earth without turning off the life support things.  The station was built for doing tests on new drugs' reactions to the human body in space.  The station is away from any huge cities or big stations.  <br>
<br>
5.)   As far as governments go, Earth and Moon are Democratic, but Mars is Communist.  That's why  Earth and Moon don't get along with Mars.  <br>
<br>
6.)   Searchers sent out by the parents of the two girls are looking for them.  After all, if your kid up and ran away, wouldn't you look for it?<br>
<br>
Well anways, that's all of them.  If you have any more questions, just ask, and thanks for all the help! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/urichied.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RichieD</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/16/02 11:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=695.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faye</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> no one would ever just abandon a space station...and if they would....they would salvage parts of it......and take all the oxygen/water/power out of it....<br>
